Which of the following commands can be used to restart the CUPS service after a configu-ration change on a server running systemd?
A)  systemctl restart cups.service
B)  systemctl restart cups
C)  systemctl reboot cups.target
D)  systemctl restart cups.target
A
A. The systemctl command is used for controlling services. In this case, restartshould be sent to the CUPS service as denoted by the name cups.service.
